PREAMBLE

The Government of the Republic of France ("France") and the Government of the

Republic of South Africa ("RSA") (hereinafter collectively referred to as "Parties" and in singular as a "Party");

RECALLING the Declaration of Intent between the Department of Agriculture,

Forestry and Fisheries of the Govemment of the Republic of South Africa, the

Department of Science and Technology of the Government of the Republic of

South Africa, and the Ministry of Agriculture, Agri Food and Forestry of the

Republic of France on Cooperation in the Field of Agricultural Education and

Research signed on 14 October 2013;

FURTHER RECALLING the Declaration of Intent between the Department of

Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries of the Republic of South Africa and the

Ministry of Agriculture, Agri Food and Forestry of France on Cooperation within the context of the G20 action plan on food price volatility and agriculture signed on 14 October 2013;

MINDFUL of the objectives of the National Development Plan of the RSA to expand the higher education sector that can contribute to rising incomes, higher productivity and the shift to a more knowledge intensive economy and to create more jobs through agricultural development;

